SIMPLE: filthiness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filthiness
<hw>Filth"i*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being
filthy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let us cleanse ourselves from all <qex>filthiness</qex> of the
flesh and spirit.</q> <rj><qau>2 Cor. vii. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is filthy, or makes filthy; foulness;
nastiness; corruption; pollution; impurity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Carry forth the <qex>filthiness</qex> out of the holy place.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Chron. xxix. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filthy</ent>⟦br⟧
